      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:49:3",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) مَنْ صَلَّى الْخَمْسَ فِي جَمَاعَةٍ فَظُنُّوا بِهِ خَيْراً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, from his<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The one who prays the five (<span class=\"iTxt\">Salāts</span>) in a <span class=\"iTxt\">Jam’at</span>, so think good about him’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfaliy, from al-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The Messenger of Allah has said, “If one performs the five Salah (prayer) in congregation you should think good about him.’”” "
        ]
      }
